-- Kenya's Samuel Wanjiru Repeats as Chicago Marathon Champion
-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 2010-10-11T05:21:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-11/kenya-s-samuel-wanjiru-repeats-as-chicago-marathon-champion.html
Samuel Wanjiru of Kenya successfully
defended his title at the Bank of America  Chicago Marathon ,
winning the race in a time of 2 hours, 6 minutes, 24 seconds.  Wanjiru, 23, finished 19 seconds ahead of London Marathon
winner Tsegaye Kebede of Ethiopia. With yesterday’s victory,
Wanjiru leads in the race for the  World Marathon Major Series 
title and its $500,000 prize.  Liliya Shobukhova of Russia also repeated as Chicago
Marathon champion by winning the women’s division yesterday in a
time of 2:20:25. Shobukhova also won this year’s London Marathon
and will earn the $500,000 bonus as winner of the World Marathon
Major Series title, which includes the results of races in
Chicago, New York, London, Berlin and Boston.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Erik Matuszewski  in New York at 
